The main, largest, bio-weapons lab in China is located about 280 meters/300 yards from the live animal meat market in Wuhan where Covid-19 is purported to originate. The main objective of this bio-weapons lab is to weaponize Sars virus into a more deadly and contagious strain. China collected virus specimens from dank bat caves around the globe, for decades, to create biological weapons. China was aware of the Covid-19 outbreak in early November 2019, and kept this secret from the world, as China sent out huge delegations and travelers across the globe and allowed billions to travel across China for the new year holiday. China kept Covid-19 data secret from WHO and CDC for months, causing delays in creating accurate tests and effective meds. Covid 19 is a SARs virus with Bat, Pangolin, and Human genetic mutations. Thousands of Chinese 'spy ships' are deployed across the globe. Fishing boats, with no fish aboard, are called 'sea phantoms'. In 2013 a Chinese 'sea phantom' spy ship ran aground in the internal sea of the Philippines after cruising along the Philippines coastlines for months. No fish aboard the fishing boat. High tech electronic gear for monitoring radio and mobile phone signals were aboard .... along with hundreds of illegally poached, endangered, Pangolins. Chinese spy ship collecting Pangolins. Imagine for a moment if a US CIA spy ship ran aground with hundreds of Pangolins onboard, then an exotic Pangolin based SARs pandemic ground zero was located next door to the CIA's largest SARs based bio-weapons lab. The world would show outrage.


NATO really needs to think long term about the current "Made in China" Covid 19 pandemic, and prepare for worse scenarios to come in the future. One possible or likely scenario is that China will keep manufacturing and releasing bio-weapon virus pandemics until they stumble across one that makes China come out stronger than the rest of the world. We should view the Covid 19 as a small speed bump in the road of life that should be a warning of a possible rough road ahead if we continue down the path of dependency upon a hostile China bent on imperial expansionism and global domination.

After the WW2 Pearl Harbor attack, the US quickly geared up US manufacturing to meet the impending crisis. Starting with steel, heavy industry, ship building, and also infrastructure such as highways, bridges, etc. NATO and our allies need to do the same today, and quickly gear up critical industry such as manufacture of medical equipment, medical supplies, and drugs. Emergency tariffs and subsidy of all critical medicine and medical gear is needed until NATO becomes a net exporter of such items. NATO needs to manufacture computers and other electronics to end dependence on China. All NATO government agencies, not just the Military, should immediately end any and all new purchase contracts of any Chinese made computers, mobile phones, monitors, notepads, radios, electronics, etc. To ease into this, NATO should adopt a uniform, and parts interchangeable, specifications for simple, slim, efficient, practical, functional, inexpensive, durable model of a mobile phone, notepad, laptop, etc.. that multiple non-Chinese companies can mass produce at many locations. Design tweaks could be made every few years to keep up with technology. Devices should be cheap, durable, rugged, readily up-gradable, repairable, and multi-functional over dazzling, artistic, or fashionable. This was how the Jeep was manufactured in WW2, by multiple auto companies; to strict specifications, with all parts interchangeable. Instead of contracting for tens of thousands of dozens of differing styled small vehicles, with endless bells and whistles, over half a million simple, chunky, cheap, functional, reliable, rugged Jeeps were quickly manufactured at many factories. NATO can do the same today, and should rapidly produce millions of mobile phones, laptops and etc., first for use by government employees, and next offered to the public. Robots could do most of the heavy lifting.

Hi everyone, I'm an italian 14 year old and the next arguments I'm going to talk about probably shouldn't be coming out of a teenager like me but I think that if we know the situation we're in we can protect ourselves.
there are TWELVE CASES OF CORONAVIRUS in my city and a person has already DIED, yet I still see groups of people hanging out and being close to one another. Needless to say, the town I live in is really small.
I haven't been going to school since february 21st and now we can't even get out of our houses if not only to get FOOD and WATER.
I've been stuck at home for two weeks straight now and can't really do anything about it if I don't wanna risk getting the virus.
Also my mom is a nurse. at this time last week and the week prior she didn't feel really good, though she kept going to work. she kept and keeps going to work, knowing that she could get the virus at any time without the equipment she and her coworkers use to protect themselves. every time she goes from patient to patient she first has to change her mask, her gloves and everything else that protects her from getting the covid-19. everyday she risks getting the virus. everyday she RISKS her LIFE by trying to save other people's lives and many people don't think this is that big of a deal.
it's not the mortality of the virus that we should be scared of but the fact that if a lot of people will keep getting it, by the end of the day there won't be many solutions we can use to help cure every individual with it.
Hospitals can't cure 7 billion people at a time.
so I'm BEGGING you.. please STOP underestimating the situation, be careful and aware of the situation you're in. please stay at home and try to entertain yourself while you're probably bored.
respect and be nice to EVERYONE. we don't need to panic. it WILL get better.
protect yourself, always be aware of your surroundings and DO NOT not listen to the precautions if you're in a red zone, like myself.
Thank you for listening to my words, have a great day and may God be with you through good and bad.

protect yourself, always be aware of your surroundings and DO NOT not listen to the precautions if you're in a red zone, like myself.
